        {
            "id": "ed57cba2-63a6-4b38-b3cb-e35ca5556cbb",
            "content": "Credentials used to access work related accounts should be stored in a password manager “database” dedicated to the position occupied by the personnel. The password manager used in the organization is Bitwarden. The password manager is the only allowed method to store credentials.",
            "tags": [
                {
                    "id": "Credentials",
                    "text": "Credentials"
                },
                {
                    "id": "Password Manager",
                    "text": "Password Manager"
                },
                {
                    "id": "Bitwarden",
                    "text": "Bitwarden"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "50c9dd58-df68-4ae2-9888-1b6ec6df02f1",
            "content": "A good password is a password that is:\n1. At least 14 char long \n2. has characters of all the following categories:\n2.1. Uppercase characters\n2.2. Lowercase characters\n2.3. Digits\n2.4. Special characters like #@<*&(^%$>![space].\n3. Is not used for another account\n4. Was not used in the last year\n5. not compromised\n6. not easy to guess\n7. not common \n8. not in a dictionary\n9. as random as possible (generated by a password manager)",
            "tags": [
                {
                    "id": "Password",
                    "text": "Password"
                },
                {
                    "id": "Password Manager",
                    "text": "Password Manager"
                },
                {
                    "id": "Accounts",
                    "text": "Accounts"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "18d799a1-c138-4d3b-99c6-663fa7176f49",
            "content": "Acceptable second factors are: TOTP Apps such as Google Authenticator, Bitwarden Authenticator A Physical Security Token YubiKey from Yubico SMS only as a backup 2nd Factor.",
            "tags": [
                {
                    "id": "2FA",
